Your Current Architecture (Very Good Now)

You now have:

app
 ├── services
 │     chat_service.py
 │
 ├── memory
 │     short_term_memory.py
 │     summary_memory.py
 │     vector_memory.py
 │     memory_router.py
 │
 ├── llm
 │     chain_factory.py
 │     prompt_factory.py
 │     llm_factory.py
 │
 └── persona
       system_prompt_builder.py

This is very close to production LLM backend architecture.

Next Step I Recommend (Huge Improvement)

Right now your memory pipeline is:

history → summarize

But the real next upgrade is:

conversation
     ↓
memory extractor (LLM)
     ↓
vector memory

Example conversation:

User: My grandma loves diamond watches

Extractor stores:

UserPreference:
grandmother likes diamond jewelry

Which your AI can remember forever across sessions.

This is how assistants become personalized.

If you want, I can show you the cleanest way to implement runtime memory extraction with your current architecture (it fits perfectly into your MemoryRouter).